Wash and dry all produce. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add garlic. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1 cup water, 1/2 tsp @harissa powder{1/2%tsp}, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until water has absorbed and bulgur is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 5.

> For 4 servings, use 2 cups water and 1 tsp harissa powder; and 1 tsp salt.

== Lemon Dill Sauce ==

While bulgur cooks, zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Pick and finely chop fronds from @dill{1/4%ounce}. Finely dice @roma tomato{1}. Trim and finely dice @persian cucumber{1}.

In a small #bowl, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, lemon zest, half the chopped dill, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Salmon ==

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add salmon skin sides down. Cook until skin is crisp and fish is almost cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}. Flip and cook until fish is opaque and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Remove from pan and set aside.

== Bulgur Salad ==

In a #medium bowl, combine cooked bulgur, tomato, cucumber, remaining chopped dill, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Divide salmon between plates and drizzle with creamy lemon dill sauce. Sprinkle with a pinch of @za'atar spice{1%tablespoon} to taste. Serve bulgur salad on the side. Squeeze juice from any remaining lemon wedges over top and serve.